description:
Overview

By Hopeless, Mellon, Herrera, & Strakhov

On a mission to find her brother, Shelby's road trip leads her to Evil Ted's Bar of the Dead. Our heroic hottie smashes the hell out of an army of zombie barkeepers. Grab the hose, kids, it's gonna be a messy night for the GearHead!

Special anniversary issue that contains three stories and a foil-stamped cover.

"Police Action, Part 3 of 3"

VIGIL has Punisher in their sights. Caught in the act of attempting to kill his target, Punisher is forced to surrender rather than fight law enforcement figures. Before he can d so, Recoil joins the battle and all bets are off.

"Bar Wars"

Punisher gets a bogus call from an informant to meet at a bar. The set-up bait is taken. Can Punisher take on a whole bar full of folks out to get him?

"Flare Up"

Punisher busts up a crack lab.
name: Police Action: Part 3

description: Punisher travels to Hawaii. While there, he gets involved with an exotic woman named Paula who informs him of an evil plot. A developers wants to use a bomb to explode a volcano in order to destroy a rival's property. Frank must stop the plotters before it is too late.
name: Lava

description:
Punisher feels the impact of Onslaught after the Helicarrier falls. How many lives will be lost in this destruction? And will Punisher be able to re-gain control after chaos reigns supreme? Itâ€™s Onslaught versus the Island of Manhattan!

Part of the Onslaught: Impact 2 storyline. Sentinels have invaded New York and Punisher wishes he had a bigger gun to take them out. But when the Sentinels attack a S.H.I.E.L.D. helicarrier, scavengers head for the downed ship in order to take whatever they can grab by any means necessary. Punisher leaps into action to save G.W. Bridge and the rest of the S.H.I.E.L.D. personnel.
name: Onslaught Impact 2: Manhattan Onslaught

description: While helping G.W. Bridge and S.H.I.E.L.D. secure the Avengers Mansion, Punisher gets assigned to protect controversial preacher William Connover. Preaching a message of mutant and human equal rights, Connover is targeted by the new Mutant Liberation Front. Punisher tangles with Deadeye in this first part to Total X-Tinction!
name: Total X-Tinction Part 1: Capitol Offenses

description: Punisher continues to square off with the new Mutant Liberation Front. Blastfurnace and Corpus Derelicti make things tough for Frank and S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Kymberly Taylor, as both find out that protecting a preacher is tougher than expected.
name: Total X-Tinction Part 2: Friend Or Foe?

description:
Misfit tries desperately to undo the damage she's caused in Oracle's command center while the rest of the Birds struggle to overcome a true life-and-death situation. Also, just how much does Lois Lane know about Oracle's operation?

Outside Denasana Prison, Mexico. Manhunter continues her battle with the metahuman prison guard Miguel begun last issue (#101). Soon, Manhunter lies prone and unconscious at the feet of the giant guard.

Barbara Gordon (aka Oracle) resumes her meeting in New York City with reporter, Lois Lane, (Mrs. Superman) reporter for the Daily Planet.

Meanwhile, at Oracleâ€™s Command Center, Dalten Towers, Misfit intercepts a frantic call from Lady Blackhawk. Trapped in a warehouse by mercenaries hired by the West Coast Crime Families to silence a potential witness against them and his daughter, Barda, Judomaster, the Huntress and Lady Blackhawk have their backs against the wall. An overwhelmed Misfit, clearly not familiar with the myriad of computer screens in Oracleâ€™s base of operations, frantically searches for a way to send help.

Back at Denasana Prison, Mexico, several members of the prison guard staff, supervised by the warden, wake the bruised and battered Manhunter for questioning.

Lois continues to fish for answers from a clearly stunned Barbara Gordon. Misfit finally makes a decision and teleports herself to the warehouse as a distracting element in the hopes that Barda, Judomaster, the Huntress and Lady Blackhawk will be able to have a fighting chance. It works well.

Meanwhile, Manhunter has had about as much of this interrogation as she will take, and strikes out at the guards (with a little help from Gypsy!) Exit guards; enter Miguel! This time, however, Manhunter decides not to throw the fight!

As Lois Lane and Barbara Gordon continue to match wits, Lois suddenly decides to make a strategic withdrawal. Have we seen the last of Lois?

A sudden phone call from Katarina (aka the Spy Smasher) tells Barbara to â€œcall off Manhunter, sheâ€™s gone rogue...

To be continued!
name: Blood and Circuits Part 3 - Freedom of Motion

description: Things heat up as Punisher takes on Blastfurnace! As tensions mount against mutants and humans in the aftermath of Onslaught, Punisher is tasked with protecting a preacher espousing a message of equal rights for mutants and humans. The new Mutant Liberation Front is out to silence this message. Total X-Tinction Part 3 of 5.
name: Total X-Tinction Part 3: Ashes, Ashes, All Fall Down

description: Punisher and X-Cutioner; allies? Punisher confronts special agent Carl Dinti about his being the X-Cutioner. The new allies must hatch a plan to break the chaos being created by the new Mutant Liberation Front in the aftermath of Onslaught. Total X-Tinction part 4 of 5.
name: Total X-Tinction Part 4: Unmasked
Total X-Tinction Part 5: Dead To Rights

description: The Punisher appears to be dead. Or is he? The U.S. Marshal's office wants to make sure that they have a body or recover the notoriously slippery Frank Castle alive. G.W. Bridge, Black Widow, Daredevil, and Spider-Man guest star as the Marvel Universe asks, "Is Punisher really gone?"
name: Dead Man Walking

description: Having survived his encounter with Simon Trask, Frank Castle is an amnesic living in an abandoned church. Can Frank leave his old life as Punisher behind or will he return to his war on crime? Final issue.
name: Double Cross

description: An effort to bring down a hiding drug lord turns the streets of Miami into a war zone. Buildings burn, the cops are near-useless and the National Guard are on the way. Sort of.
name: Fortress Miami: Part 1

description: With a drug war dragging on in Miami, Florida, Punisher must fight a war on two fronts by eluding National Guardsmen and taking on Garland and General Carranza's men.
name: Fortress Miami Part 2: Hammered

description: Punisher tracks Carranza to a luxurious prison compound in Bosqueverde. While Carranza tries to keep a low profile in the lap of luxury, Punisher seeks to snuff the former dictator out. Frank has to storm the near impenetrable camp to dish out his punishment.
name: Fortress Miami Part 3: The Silk Noose

description: Ragged and on the run, Punisher must improvise while Carranza's men are in pursuit. The jungles of Bosqueverde provide Frank with the perfect weapon to get his plan for taking out Carranza back on track. Kidnapping a member of the security force, Punisher is able to taunt and draw out his prey.
name: Fortress Miami Part 4: Razor's Edge

description: A terrified neighborhood appeals to Frank to clear it from dangerous criminals. How can he say no? But the citizens are going to have to live with what they requested...
name: Killing Streets

description:
"No Rules, Part I"

After a long drawn-out battle, Punisher is force to team-up with a low life gangster named Grisholm in order to survive their inadvertently breaking up a chain-match fight! Punisher and Grisholm must fight the contestants and a mad crowd in an insane brawl for survival.
name: No Rules Part 1

description:
"No Rules, Part II"

The Punisher and gangster Grisholm find themselves prisoner to Irish Joe. Both are forced to an underground fight to the death in order to recoup loses incurred by their accidental intrusion last issue. Punsiher and Grisholm must once again work together to overcome the situation. But can Frank find it in his heart to thank Grisholm by letting him go instead of killing him?
name: No Rules Part 2: No Mercy

description:
"Raving Beauty"

Hell hath no fury like a woman/former beauty queen/actress scorned! Life didn't turn out so well for Cheryl after she came in second place for Miss America. Acting and tough times eventually led to drugs, porn movie acting, and prostitution. Determined to make the people who led her down the wrong path pay, Cheryl strikes out for vengeance. A chance meeting with the Punisher saves her life, but violence begets more violence.
name: Raving Beauty

description: Punisher is back in town and looking to remind the criminals of NYC why they should fear him. After taking on terrorists who have hijacked a train full of innocents, Micro begins to worry that Punisher is needlessly putting people at risk. While Micro tries to find a way to solve this problem, Punisher is on the lookout for a new drug lord named Cringe.
name: The Devil's Secret Name

description: Microchip thinks he may have a solution to his Punisher problem: convincing Carlos Cruz to become the new Punisher! Meanwhile, Punisher is still tracking down information about the new drug lord Cringe while trying to figure out where Micro is.
name: Armies Of The Night

description:
Tommy, Wildcat's son, continues his fight against Vandal Savage. He lets his savage nature out as they both draw blood.

In Blue Valley, the Justice Society continues to protect family members from the Nazis and his crew. The same goes in Philadelphia. Damage cuts loose with his power, accidentally hitting Liberty Belle with the backlash of his explosion.

Savage is about to get the upper hand on Tommy when Wildcat comes two. All three are knocked out the window to continue the fight outside.

In Philly, Hourman is furious with Damage. He blames him for being careless. He accuses him of trying to follow in his father's footsteps on top of the fact that he's still wearing his mask. Liberty Belle appears to be somewhat okay. Captain Nazi grabs Damage and removes the mask. Damage's face appears to be disfigured as he tries to cover it. Liberty Belle simply picks up the mask and hands it back to Damage.

Wildcat and Tommy are still struggling to defeat Savage. It's not until a fire truck coming at full speed runs right into him that the fight is over.

With all the fights over, the Justice Society returns to their headquarters. Alan Scott, Jay Garrick, and Hawkman ask Powergirl if she'd be willing to become the chairwoman of the Justice Society. He responds with a "Hell yes." Ted tells Tommy he can be known as "Wildcat" also. He figures if there can be more than one Green Lantern or Flash, there can be more than one Wildcat.

In Arkham Asylum, Doctor Destiny seems to have a Dream Girl in his custody. She mumbles, "Star Boy...where are you?"
name: The Next Age: Chapter 4

description: Punisher "teams-up" with a crack dealer named Teevee to find out the true identity of Cringe. Using Teevee as a human bomb, Punisher sends his new friend out into the world to find out more information. Unbeknownst to Punisher, Microchip begins training his new Punisher, Carlos Cruz.
name: Bury Me Deep

description:
Giant-sized anniversary issue. Punisher makes it 100, but can he make it out of this issue alive? This issue features two stories and a foil variant cover.

"The Cage"

After finding out Cringe is Microchip, Punisher finds himself trapped in a reconstruction of his old home while being assaulted with home videos of his family. This is an extreme intervention for Frank on Microchip's behalf! Meanwhile, Carlos is out on the street making the best of his new life as the Punisher.

"Computers to Kill by"

Microchip gets his own seven page story! When computers start killing people, who would you call?
name: The Cage

description: Microchip is finding life as Cringe presents its own unique set of challenges. His new Punisher Carlos Cruz fights for survival underwater against Hog. Microchip also finds imprisoning Punisher to be difficult, especially when he starts to believes that his radical imprisonment therapy may have cause Frank to commit suicide! To make matters worse, the Carbone crime family has hired none other than the notorious assassin Bullseye to take down Punisher.
name: Dead Tomorrows

description: Rosalie Carbone has hired Bullseye to end her Punisher problem. Despite his best efforts to escape, Frank is still imprisoned in Microchips warehouse. Punisher's new tech-buddies Ponygirl and Mouse begin to work on a way to release Frank before the oncoming violence descends on everyone.
name: Under The Gun

description:
Â 
DETECTIVE COMICS ships twice in March to present 'The Siege,' a nail-biting 2-part suspense story written by Stuart Moore (FIRESTORM, Punisher X-Mas Special) and Andy Clarke (BATMAN: FACE THE FACE)! In issue #829, a costumed terrorist called VOX plans to blow up Wayne Tower - and he's trapped Bruce Wayne in a top-floor conference room. Aided only by his mentor's radioed instructions, Robin must face the bomber alone! And in the conclusion in #830, Robin faces certain death as massive explosions rock Wayne Tower. Only Bruce Wayne can stop the terrorist - but changing to Batman will mean revealing his dual identity! Â  Â 
Â 
Robin is covered with liquid explosives as Vox runs away. Bruce reminds him that C4 can only be detonated when it's fully solid and that it requires a blasting cap. Robin notices the cap but cannot move his arem to reach it. Bruce asks what floor he's on then tells him of another "secret" room. Another explosion goes off so Gordon sends in his men. Inside the room, Bruce tells Robin to find a small blowtorch and melt off the explosives. C4 doesn't explode under flame, just from a major impact. Robin is able to remove the cap and throw it out into the hall just as it goes off.

Bruce is still unable to fully do anything as the dignitaries continue to fight and blame each other for the current events. He tries to rally them together with a little speech but it has little effect. He lets off a smoke bomb and jumps down the stairwell. Now dressed as Batman, he faces off against Vox. The fight goes on and finally Robin arrives. Vox refuses to give up. He blasts through a window, taking Batman with him. Batman is able to shoot a line that attaches to the building. As they hang there, Vox tells Batman that he thought Batman would understand that the injustice needs to be stopped. Batman tells him that no injustice is worth the lives of innocents. Vox thinks about this, tells him he's right and punches him. The punch causes Batman to let go of him and Vox falls to his death.

The only good thing to come out of this is the hope that the dignitaries have been brought together now and perhaps this is the first step in creating a new better world.
name: Siege (Part 2)

description:
The final shots have been fired. The Civil War has ended. A victor has emerged. Now, S.H.I.E.L.D. has prepared the BATTLE DAMAGE REPORT, an intelligence dossier assessing the impact of the war and the dangers the nation still faces. BATTLE DAMAGE REPORT provides a closing chapter to CIVIL WAR and a glimpse of the new status quo of the Marvel Universe!

A whopping 64 page handbook covering the current status of just about every character in the Marvel Universe. This is the place to find out what everyone is up to. Who fought on which side. Who was injured or incarcerated. Everything you wanted to know but were afraid to ask. Except why Tony Stark was such a jerk.

Ash fights Gabriel as is late for a date.

Pin up by Kevin Nowlan.
name: Church of the Poison Mind

description:
The story takes place in the future during a nuclear winter and also in the past before Ashley Quinn becomes "Ash".

Has a pin up gallery that includes: Jim Calafiore, Rick Leonardi, J.H. Williams and ChrisCross.
name: Time to Die?

description: Punisher's friend Sammy asks Punisher to visit Alaska to investigate a strange base he has found in the wilderness. However, the people operating the base don't want him to investigate and they shoot down their helicopter. Alone and inured in the wilderness, Frank must survive the elements to in order to get to the bottom of this situation.
name: Survival: Part 1

description: Stranded in the Alaskan wilderness, Frank fights his way towards a private army compound he was hired to investigate. Sammy, the pilot, survived the crash, but is now a prisoner of the private army.
name: Survival: Part 2

description: The Punisher takes on a private army complex in the Alaskan wilderness. Not only does he have to stop the army from forcibly taking Kamchatka's resources, but he also has to save his friend Sammy and a Native American named Chagee.
name: Survival: Part 3

description: A priest with a dark past spots Frank Castle sitting in his church. Frank is not pursuing him and does not know of his past. However, the priest becomes paranoid and begins to recount his crimes and confess his sins awaiting judgement from the Punisher.
name: Last Confession

description: The Punisher tracks down Lorga, a local crime boss, thanks to some well-sourced information from an accountant. However, two cops are preparing to raid the Punisher's hotel room and arrest him. One cop is an honest cop, while the other cop is on the take from Lorga.
name: Bodies of Evidence

description:
"Firefight, Part 1"

Corrupt real estate mogul Ramsey Sutherland III manages to get his arsonist uncle Ray out of a state mental health facility. This isn't a measure of good faith: he intends to use him for a job! The Punisher must deal with this newly released menace before an entire neighborhood literally explodes.
name: Firefight: Part 1

description:
"Firefight, Part 2"

Punisher saves people from the burning building, but blacks outs afterwards. In police custody on the scene, Frank watches as the neighborhood burns. VIGIL, the vigilante hunting unit, gets involved when they hear Frank contact Micro over the CB system.
name: Firefight: Part 2

description: New York is going up in flames thanks to a revenge-crazed arsonist. Frank gains some allies in New York's finest. Desperate to stop the chaos, firemen give him what help they can.
name: Firefight: Part 3

description:
Overview

V.I.G.I.L. takes aim at Punisher after their funding is threatened for failing to come up with any major arrests. Lt. Blackwell blames one man: Frank Castle. The Punisher must escape a web of smugglerss and an organization with a vendetta against him.
name: Suicide Run Part 0: Smoke & Fire

description:
"Countdown 4"

Freed from Microchips insane intervention prison, Frank, Mouse, and Ponygirl go into hiding. Microchip's new Punisher Carlos Cruz goes toe-to-toe with Bullseye. Carlos has to survive if Microchip's plan can continue. But with Frank on the loose, how long can Microchip go unchecked?

Continued in Punisher War Journal #79
name: Countdown 4: The Butcher's Block

description:
Continued from: Punisher War Zone #41

"Countdown 1: The Murder Men"

Punisher doubts his mission and purpose and tries to surrender to the police. At the last moment, the now deposed Kingpin offers Frank a chance at revenge. Frank accepts and starts weeding out those on the Kinpin's list.

Continued in: Punisher War Journal #80

This is the last issue of this series. Punisher would continue in the next volume of Punisher would be published in November 1995. Between the ending of this final issue and the beginning of his next series, the Punisher begins to believe Nick Fury orchestrated his family's death. This happened during the 1995 Double Edge Summer Event. This leads directly to his next series, where Punisher is sent to the electric chair for killing Nick Fury.
name: Countdown 1: The Murder Men

description: Continued from: The Punisher #103
name: Countdown 3: House of the Dead
Into Into Infinity / If I Should Die--

description: Part of the Black September crossover
name: Day For Night

description: Shortly before the symbiote, invasion the protector of the stargate, who happened to be a symbiote very similar to venom, meddled with the stargate switching it on. This allowed the being known as Rune to enter the marvel universe. Rune kills the symbiotes host but the symbiote forces itself on rune. Sometime later, in symbiote invasion venom became a traitor and killed many other symbiotes to protect earth at spiderman's side along with a hero known as the scarlet spider. Upon seeing this, the symbiote who became one with rune set out to punish the traitor by commiting sever ghastley murders and leaving venom's name on the nearest walls with the victom's blood. S.H.I.E.L.D. agents set out and in a brief battle with venom accidentally give away all the imformation of the killer. Venom searches for the killer and meets him. The symbiotic rune easily overpowers venom, poisons him with a bite into his neck and tells him that he will suffer by watching his mate, Ann Weying, die at his hand and then that he will die and departs. Now a weakened venom must batlle both the S.H.I.E.L.D. agents and a symbiotic god. Just on question: how can anyone manage that?
name: Rune-Venom

description: Peaceful family man Frank Castle can't understand why he's having such violent dreams. They seem to match up with reality but there are innocent explanations. Maybe he just needs to relax more.
name: Psychoville U.S.A. Part 2: Happy Days
Psychoville U.S.A. Part 3: My Two Dads
Psychoville U.S.A. Part 4: Father Knows Best

description: An expertise in architecture is being used for murder. That makes the Punisher mad.
name: The Jericho Syndrome

description: This is it! The double-sized finale! America strikes back against the Liberators, as ace artist Bryan Hitch draws every single super hero in the Ultimate Universe in combat to free the United States! Plus: the true fate of Thor, the return of the Defenders, and every major plotline from the Ultimates (since its inception) comes together at last. If ever there was a big one you should not miss...Ultimates 2 #12 is it! If you do but one thing with your life: read this comic! And don't forget -this cataclysmic story leads straight into Ultimates 3 #1, coming soon! Part 6 (of 6).
name: The Avengers

description: The Punisher works with others to bring down a criminal who uses architectual knowledge for various crimes.
name: The Jericho Syndrome Part 3

description:
He canâ€™t fly, shoot lasers from his eyes, or bench-press cars, but he might be the more dangerous than Hyperion, Doctor Spectrum, and Power Princess rolled into one.

But how will the vigilante known as Nighthawk respond when heâ€™s asked to join the Squadron Supreme?
name: Questions of Loyalty

description:
Brief Description:

Nurse Annie and her son arrive at the Xavier Institute for Higher Learning, where they are welcomes by Paige. Annie doesnâ€™t like mutants and is concerned for her sonâ€™s safety. Right then the X-Men return from their mission and Xavier telepathically contacts Husk to meet them in the infirmary as they have wounded aboard. While Xavier tends to Icemanâ€˜s injuries, Annie tries to deal with Warrenâ€˜s broken limbs, though suddenly Stacy becomes angry. She reveals that she is able to â€œseeâ€œ othersâ€™ pheromones and obviously Husk has a crush on Warren. After being humiliated in front of everyone present, Paige starts to cry and leaves the room. However when Warren accuses Stacy of jealousy, she too is shocked and leaves. Outside on the school grounds, Wolverine tells the Juggernaut that if he dares to attack his friends in their home, he will show no mercy at all. Wolverine walks away, but Sammy and Carter stay behind, gazing up at the Juggernaut in awe, they think he is cool. Xavier enters the astral plane to pull back the mind of the comatose Havok, but he finds himself almost pulled into Alex's pain and loneliness and has to turn back. Yet he promises to Annie that he will keep trying. Charles offers Annie a position at the Institute, assuring her that the fact that she is not a mutant fits with his personal philosophy of cooperation between the races. She hesitantly accepts. Later Annie walks to Huskâ€™s room to ask if she is okay. Paige is angry: she tells Annie that it is obvious that she doesn't care about mutants, and questions why she decided to try to comfort her in the first place. Annie admits that she doesn't generally like mutants, but insists that she doesn't like to see anyone, human or mutant, in emotional pain. Paige thanks her but prefers to be left alone. Annie walks back to her room. As she enters, she thinks to herself that she must eventually get over her mutant prejudice for "obvious reasons." Annie sits down on the bed and watches as Carter telekinetically lifts his toys into the air.

Full Synopsis:

Annie and her son Carter walk through the gates of the Xavier Institute for Higher Learning. Carter is amazed by the many mutants running around, though his mother tells him not to stare. Annie is uncomfortable: she "has her reasons" for disliking mutants. Paige meets Annie at the school's entrance and greets her. She introduces herself and explains that Scott was called away and couldnâ€™t welcome her. As Paige tends to Carter, Annie asks Paige what her mutant power is and if it is potentially harmful to the boy. Husk assures her that her son is in no danger, just as the Blackbird roars over the school grounds. Carter and Annie are stunned, but Paige tells them that the Shi'ar warship that hovered above the school a few weeks ago was even more exciting. Husk suddenly touches her forehead as if she has a headache, and Annie asks if she is alright. However she is just receiving a telepathic message from Xavier, who tells her to ask Annie to use her nursing skills in attending to the wounded X-Men aboard the craft. Annie agrees, but refuses to let Xavier telepathically tell her the details of their injuries.

Paige, Annie and Carter enter the recovery room where Iceman and Archangel are lying on hospital beds. Wolverine, Stacy X, Nightcrawler, Juggernaut, and Sammy are also in the room. Xavier introduces himself and thanks Annie for helping. She mentions that she used to work in an emergency room and immediately inspects Bobby's chest wound, which, to her surprise, is filled with ice. Bobby explains that it is his mutant power and Annie tells him that his ice is likely the only thing keeping the wound from killing him. She offers to stitch the wound for him, but Iceman wants the professor to do it. Annie once more repeats her offer, telling that she is fully qualified for such a task but he insists that Xavier does it.

Stacy calls Annie over to take a look at Warren's broken arm and leg. The nurse inspects him and thinks that he must be in great pain, though Warren claims he is fine. Stacy however tells the truth, he is just playing the tough guy, while during the flight he nearly fainted. Also standing at his bedside, Husk notices aloud that Warren's skin has regained its natural color, though in his current condition Warren does not care that much about it. Annie asks for Stacy to get out of the way, though suddenly the young mutant becomes angry, accusing Husk of never having "heard of a bra." Paige looking rather puzzled, asks if she was talking to her. Juggernaut, Wolverine, and Sammy look on with amusement. Stacy explodes at Husk, and a vicious verbal brawl ensues. Paige claims that she is simply concerned for her friend Warren, but Stacy disagrees: she can see pheromones, and Husk's pheromones show an obvious attraction to Archangel. Paige is speechless, and runs out of the room in tears. Stacy begins to gloat, but Warren gives her a harsh admonishment for her cruelty and accuses her of being jealous. She leaves in a rage, claiming that she will go watch porn in her room.

Annie comments on her being an interesting woman, and Nightcrawler agrees that she makes his head hurt. Xavier compliments Annie on her calmness through the chaos of the situation. He suddenly remembers the recent events involving Alex being brought to the Institute. At the mention of their former teammate, the X-Men in the room react with joy and disbelief. Annie explains Alex's time in the convalescent home while Xavier finishes stitching Bobby's wound. Havok, or actually his catatonic body, is in an adjacent room, and Xavier prepares to telepathically free Alex from his comatose state. The team debates whether or not they should contact Lorna Dane to tell her that Alex has been found. Warren thinks that this should be Cyclopsâ€˜ decision, as shortly before Alex â€œdiedâ€œ, he and Lorna had broke up. Annie is amazed by what Xavier is trying to do. She asks the X-Men if Xavier can really restore Alex and Kurt comments that he hopes so.

On the school grounds, Wolverine approaches Juggernaut with Sammy and Carter at his side. He asks Cain where he thinks he is going, and the Juggernaut replies that he is an invited guest here. Logan however points out that he is against Cain being there and should he dare to attack him and his friends in their home, he will show no mercy at all. Logan reminds Juggernaut that he defeated Magneto, who was many times stronger than Cain. Wolverine walks away, and Juggernaut starts to cure at him, until he gets away of the two youngsters still gazing up at him in wonder. Cain tells them to get lost, and proceeds to steal a kid's basketball and slam dunk it. Sammy and Carter watch in awe, remarking that Juggernaut is "so cool."

On the Astral Plane, Xavier attempts to reach Alex's mind and follows a red line through a black void of nothing. At a certain point the surroundings change and the black environment seems to be torn apart, revealing a bright light. The red line enters that area, though it becomes erratic. Xavier hears screams from the area of light and yells out to Alex that he can feels his pain. He finds that Alex's pain and loneliness are so strong that he cannot come closer or he will be sucked into Alex's anguish. Xavier urges his student to reach out to him. In the physical world, a tear wells up in the Professor's eye. After three hours, he finally leaves the Astral Plane, finding that only Annie is still in the room watching him. He tells her that despite his best efforts, he cannot reach Alex, but swears to keep trying after a short rest.

The nurse asks the professor is he is alright, but he is not. He admits that it is hard for him to find himself unable to help one of his students. Surely she as a mother can relate. Charles offers Annie a position at the Institute, assuring her that the fact that she is not a mutant fits with his personal philosophy of cooperation between the races. Xavier notices that her last name, "Ghazikhanian" is Armenian, and asks her if her parents ever spoke of the Turkish massacres of the Armenians at the turn of the twentieth century. Annie replies that they did, and Xavier tells her that she, like everyone, has some experience with racial and cultural oppression, whether it be as oppressor or oppressed. He further explains that he does not believe that mankind was placed on the earth to wipe each other out, and tells her that the races of the world must learn to live together, not apart. Xavier offers his hand to her, asking her to work with him. She hesitantly shakes it.

Somewhat later, Annie is walking around the mansion, still thinking about her dislike of mutants. Yet she is also feeling guilty and ashamed about it. A wise woman once told her that â€œfeelings areâ€œ, meaning that they have meaning and importance and to deny them or lying about them, would only mean to never understand them. Annie knocks at Husk's room and asks if she is okay. Paige is angry: she tells Annie that it is obvious that she doesn't care about mutants, and questions why she decided to try to comfort her in the first place. Annie admits that she doesn't generally like mutants, but insists that she doesn't like to see anyone, human or mutant, in emotional pain, especially such pain that Paige is going through right now. Paige thanks her, but prefers to be left alone and closes the door.

Annie walks back to her room. As she enters, she thinks to herself that she must eventually get over her mutant prejudice for "obvious reasons." Annie sits down on the bed and watches as Carter telekinetically lifts his toys into the air.
name: Annie's Moving Story

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The Legion of Super-Heroes, severely diminished in number due to various missions, are briefed on the five most dangerous super-villains of the galaxy. They also learn that a living cloud called the Sun-Eater is going through the galaxy, eating stars. The Legion try to recruit superheroes, but to no avail. Feeling like they have no choice, they decide to recruit the five dangerous super-villains to aid in their endeavor. The five villains each agree to help since if they don't, they would perish anyway.

Two-Face â€“ Double Cross

A Knightfall crossover. As Robin and Alfred hold vigil over Bruce Wayneâ€™s broken body, Robin recounts a story of three weeks earlier, where he felt just as helpless. Two-Face returns to Gotham, and takes over â€œLegsâ€ Lymanâ€™s gang. Batman investigates, but asks Robin to stay out of this case. With soldiers, he sets a trap for Batman. By tricking Batman to take a specific bridge across the river, Two-Face detonates an explosion, forcing the Batmobile into the river.

The Kobra Kronicles, Part 2: Acute Schizophrenia Paranoia Blues

Peacemaker and Deathstroke are fighting off Kobra troops from last issue. They make their escape, and get separated. Peacemaker finds two children while fighting off a Kobra trooper mutated into a snake creature. Deathstroke arrives in the nick of time, and the kill the mutated Kobra trooper. On his body, they find a lead for an electronics fair in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile, Kobra hires Deadshot to kill Peacemaker and Deathstroke.

Jade and Obsidian â€“ Image is Everything

Jade was hired to use her power and act in a commercial for a perfume, and Jade invites Obsidian to watch the results. When leaving, Jade, Obsidian, and the film crew are trapped in a never-ending world of Escher-like proportions. The creator of this trap is named Mister McEscher, a film creator jealous of Jade. Jade and Obsidian defeat McEscher, but the commercial crew offer him a tryout for a soda commercial.

description:
Kyle continues to fight Grayven. After getting distracted by a message from Guy about his mother's poor condition, Grayven was able to get a hold of Kyle from behind. He has his hands wrapped around his neck and Kyle cannot break free. Grayven mentions that his friends will be happy with one less obstacle once Kyle is dead. It seems Grayven has forgotten about Donna Troy as she smashes him from behind. All Kyle knows is he needs to get back to Earth now. His message from Guy got cut off. He knows Grayven is somehow involved and demands to know what's happening to his mother. Kyle's not going to stand for someone threatening his mother again. He says he'll do anything to prevent going through that again.

As Kyle grabs hold of Grayven and asks him again, Grayven just smiles at him. Kyle told him he gave him a chance. His hands grab hold of Grayven's head on either side and his hands begin to glow brighter and brighter. Grayven begs him to stop as there is a big blast. Grayven is out. Donna asks Kyle if he's dead and he responds that he doesn't know or care. He puts him in an energy bubble and sends him off to the Guardians.

Donna and Kyle begin to return to Earth when a Monitor appears before them. The Monitor says that Kyle poses a "grave danger" and should be destroyed along with the other anomalies. As he prepares to blast Kyle, Kyle shoots first. The monitor appears to have been vaporized but has been pulled back to the other Monitors. They tell him this is not the time to react. When that time comes, they will act together.

Kyle and Donna arrive at his mother's hospital room. Guy, Kilowog, and Soranik are there. Guy tells him that everyone did everything that they could. Kyle's mom is dead. As Donna embraces him, trying to offer some comfort, Kyle realizes that it doesn't have to be this way. He can fix things. Using his power, he reanimates his mom. As she comes to and talks to him, she realizes something isn't right. She tells him he needs to accept what has happened and that she loves him. Kyle removes the power as she asks and she crumples into his arms.

At the funeral, Kyle thinks about everything that had to be done, all the preparations. The man claiming to be his father never showed. He figures that's a good thing. He now has to figure out what to do with her possessions and sell her house. Eventually he finds himself alone.

Back at the artists' retreat, his friends try to console them in their way. As he sits in his studio, his neighbor leaves a painting she did for him. A single rose with the words, "So sorry for your loss." Kyle is still distraught with all that has happened. He has painted pictures of all the women in his life that he has lost: Alex, Donna, Jade, and his mother. He cannot help but feel that with everything he has recently gone through, it's not over yet.

Out in the far reaches of space, five yellow rings fly together then split apart, searching for their new bearers. The caption says: "To be continued this summer in Green Lantern: Sinestro Corps Special."
name: Burying the Past

description:
Lex meets with a U.S. Army General as he gives him an enormous platoon of G.I. Robot units after winning the defense contract. Lex then gets a phone call about his robotic bat that is trying to infiltrate Batman's "lair." It's attached itself to unidentified aircraft that most likely belongs to Batman.

At the Batcave, Batman arrives in his new plane. As he goes over the plans of the military command base to try to figure out what Lex is up to, the robotic bat begins to make its move. It works its way to a control pad and types in, "KILL." The bat-plane starts up and fires a missle at Batman and Alfred. Batman falls back into the deep of the cave.

At the army base, Lex is still pleased with the possibility of what his robotic bat will accomplish. He tells the general that there's been a change in plans. He's taking the base and robots back. He gives a counter-command to the G.I. Robots and gives the command to allow the general just enough time to run out screaming or he will be vaporized.

Batman survives his fall by falling in twenty feet of bat guano. It literally "stinks." Batman has to use a breathing mask to get away from the smell of ammonia. He can hear the bat-plane still trying to kill any available targets. It seems to have Alfred in its sights. Batman manages to jump onto the plane as it passes by. He accesses the controls and returns it to manual control. Using the plane's sensors, he finds the robotic bat that caused this problem. It's making its way to the batmobile. Alfred simply stomps on it.

In Gothom, Captain James Gordon is in a patrol car with an officer. For some reason traffic is incredibly backed up. A radio transmission starts up on all channels. It tells them that Democracy isn't working. It goes on and on. Gordon gets out of the squad car and walks up the street. He sees Lex on a jumbotron as he finishes his speech and says he is going to be making some changes.
name: Rules of Engagement: Part 4
